Paper: hep-th/9208034

Date: 1992-08-12

Title: Einstein Gravity in 2+1 Dimensions from a Gauge Model with Symmetry

BreakingAuthors: R. Brooks, D. Cangemi and M. Crescimanno

Comments: 10 pages, MIT preprint CTP#2129

Einstein Gravity in 2+1 dimensions arises as a consequence of the equationsof motion of a gauge model in an external metric. Newton's constant appears asan order parameter of a spontaneously broken discrete symmetry. Matter iscoupled in a straightforward way.